author: Zandile
text: Woolies pride themselves on their customer services and exchange and refund policy yet this particular manager behaves contrary to that. If the boots were not in a sellable condition I wouldn't have minded for them to be checked by H/O

author: Zandile
text: I work in the CBD and I will again have to go the Woolies in Adderly street. How will now walk in there with the same comfort and reliability as before??????

author: Zandile
text: Vuyo exchanged the boots only when I started to raise my voice and wanted more people to inspect. Why only after I was a total b%$ did she agree to authorise. I almost had a panic attack at the store because I was shaking and teary. This is not the treatment I expected from W

author: Zandile
text: Never have I felt so mistreated!!!! I've been going to Woolies Adderly for more than 6 years. I've exchanged clothing and shoes before, always with a slip and in good condition. I respect the cashiers and their jobs and I've never have been an unreasonable customer.

author: Zandile
text: When I agreed for another pair of eyes to check, she then said, fine, she'll authorise. At this time I'm fuming because she humiliated me and more than that insinuated I wore the boots even though there are no signs of wearing them. I was so embarrassed!

author: Zandile
text: Vuyo came back & claimed I wore them again, although the cashier and I see no difference, she pointed out marks in the heel that were not visible. She suggested we should get someone else to inspect & I was only too glad for another person to check because I knew she was lying.

author: Zandile
text: At this point, I'm upset but calm. The cashier on Vuyo's instruction took another pair on the shelf to compare the heels, upon inspecting she agreed that the shoes look the same underneath which was the only area needed to be checked, because the boots were in perfect condition.

author: Zandile
text: A lady named Vuyo, started to interrogate me insisting I had worn the boots. When I explained that I tried them on yes, but did not leave the house because I couldn't walk in them, she started coming up with all sorts of stories of how and where I wore the boots.
